author: Warhammer
description:
The Dominator Engines bellow forth from their masters' forges, filled with daemonic energies and clad in the toughest plate armour. Can Dan tackle this bull and show you how to paint such a beast in all its glory? Stay tuned to find out!

Here’s a list of the paints we used in today’s video:

Metals

Layer:
Hashut Copper
Canoptek Alloy
Stormhost Silver
Warplock Bronze

Green Daemonic Fire and Smoke

Base:
Abaddon Black
Caliban Green 
Corax White 
Screamer Pink
Naggaroth Night

Layer:
Gauss Blaster Green
Warpstone Glow

Technical:
Lahmian Medium 

Tools:
Small Base STC
Medium Drybrush STC
Medium Layer STC
Medium Shade

If you enjoyed this and want to learn more, our YouTube channel has an array of beginner-friendly videos to get you started.
